<p>Viral modifications of infected plants also impact the dynamics of the vector population. In particular, viral modifications lead to relative aggregation of the vector on healthy or infected plants. This, in turn, influences the spread of the virus. Analysis of the Markov chain (Fig. 
 <xref rid="ecy2725-fig-0001" ref-type="fig">1</xref>B) leads to expressions for the probability of settling on susceptible (
 <italic>S</italic>) vs. infected (
 <italic>I</italic>) plants, denoted 
 <italic>F</italic>
 <sub>
  <italic>S</italic>
 </sub> and 
 <italic>F</italic>
 <sub>
  <italic>I</italic>
 </sub>, respectively (derived in Appendix 
 <xref rid="ecy2725-sup-0004" ref-type="supplementary-material">S4</xref>):
 <disp-formula id="ecy2725-disp-0004">
  <label>(4)</label>
  <math id="nlm-math-6">
   <mrow>
    <msub>
     <mi>F</mi>
     <mi>S</mi>
    </msub>
    <mo>=</mo>
    <mi>S</mi>
    <mo stretchy="false">/</mo>
    <mrow>
     <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>
     <mi>S</mi>
     <mo>+</mo>
     <mi mathvariant="normal">ν</mi>
     <mi mathvariant="normal">ε</mi>
     <mi>I</mi>
     <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>
    </mrow>
    <mo>=</mo>
    <mrow>
     <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>
     <mn>1</mn>
     <mo>−</mo>
     <mover accent="true">
      <mi>i</mi>
      <mo stretchy="false">~</mo>
     </mover>
     <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>
    </mrow>
    <mo stretchy="false">/</mo>
    <mrow>
     <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>
     <mn>1</mn>
     <mo>−</mo>
     <mover accent="true">
      <mi>i</mi>
      <mo stretchy="false">~</mo>
     </mover>
     <mrow>
      <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>
      <mn>1</mn>
      <mo>−</mo>
      <mi mathvariant="normal">ε</mi>
      <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>
     </mrow>
     <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>
    </mrow>
    <mo>,</mo>
   </mrow>
  </math>
 </disp-formula>
 <disp-formula id="ecy2725-disp-0005">
  <label>(5)</label>
  <math id="nlm-math-7">
